fields.description: Resolve customer complaints via phone, email, mail, or social media. Use telephones to reach out to customers and verify account information. Greet customers warmly and ascertain problem or reason for calling. Assist with placement of orders, refunds, or exchanges.
fields.title: Customer Service Representative

fields.description: Supervise Customer Service Representatives. Handle scheduling and problem escalation.
fields.title: Customer Service Supervisor

fields.description: Full-stack software developer with extensive experience in Ruby on Rails, PHP, and custom WP development (among other things).
fields.title: Senior Web Developer

3-5 years of experience in customer service.
Deep knowledge of HTML, CSS, JavaScript, AJAX, and PHP
Solid experience with custom WordPress development

fields.definition: Takes responsibility for decisions made, actions taken, and assignments completed; takes ownership for one's performance.
fields.name: Accountability

fields.definition: Able to modify one's own behavioral style to respond to the needs of others while maintaining one's own objectives and sense of dignity.
fields.name: Adaptability

fields.definition: Able to use a systematic approach in solving problems through analysis of problem and evaluation of alternate solutions; use logic, mathematics, or other problem solving tools in data analysis or in generating solutions.
fields.name: Analytical Problem Solving

fields.definition: Insight into motivation based on general career goals.
fields.name: Career

fields.definition: Able to understand process improvements and implement new procedures to achieve the goals of the change.
fields.name: Change Introduction/Adoption

fields.definition: Shows respect and value for the skills, experiences, creativity, and contributions of group members. Able to work with others in a joint intellectual effort with colleagues and customers.
fields.name: Collaboration

fields.definition: Able to clearly present information through the spoken word; influence or persuade others through oral presentation in positive or negative circumstances; listen well.
fields.name: Communication (Verbal)

fields.definition: Able to write clearly and effectively present ideas and to document activities; to read and interpret written information.
fields.name: Communication (Written)

fields.definition: Able to identify and handle conflicts sensibly, fairly, and efficiently.
fields.name: Conflict Resolution

fields.definition: Able to develop unique and novel solutions to problems; use intuition and a new way of thinking to give birth to new ideas; to present information in an attention-getting and interesting manner.
fields.name: Creativity

fields.definition: Keeps internal and/or external customers in mind at all times. Strives to proactively address customer concerns and needs.  Assists business partners and customers  achieve their work goals via application of their own skills and knowledge; strives to provide consistent customer satisfaction.
fields.name: Customer Service

fields.definition: Able to make decisions on available information and take action; make commitments and not change decisions when challenged; deal with emergencies as necessary.
fields.name: Decision Making

fields.definition: Able to give another party a certain degree of discretion that's not inherent in their role--the right to make decisions that are officially tied to your role and for which you are ultimately responsible. Can delegate with forethought and planning in a way that capitalizes on opportunities.
fields.name: Delegation

fields.definition: Able to pay attention to the details and can make a conscious effort to understand causes instead of just the effects. Patience and determination to explore the problem and all of its elements until the reasoning has been found so that it can be resolved accurately.
fields.name: Detail-Oriented

fields.definition: Monitoring a job, enquiry, sale, etc., to get feedback on the schedule, requirements, effectiveness, or other such factors. Checks for errors and takes corrective action as needed so that deviation from standards are minimized and stated goals of the organization are achieved.
fields.name: Follow up and Control

fields.definition: Quick to point out the contributions of others and slow to seek attention for their own. They share credit, emphasize team over self, and define success collectively rather than individually.
fields.name: Humble

fields.definition: A manageable and sustainable commitment to doing a job well and going above and beyond when it is truly required. Always looking for more things to do, more to learn, more responsibility to take on. Self-motivated and diligent. Constantly thinking about the next step and the next opportunity. Loathe the idea that they might be perceived as slackers.
fields.name: Hungry

fields.definition: Evaluates, selects and acts on strategies for solving problems and meeting objectives before being asked to do so. Begins actions to influence events and/or to achieve goals. Sees opportunities for action and acts on them.
fields.name: Initiative

fields.definition: Having the character to do the right thing when no one else is around. Chooses commitments responsibly and follows through on those commitments to completion. Refrains from cheating and lying. Sets appropriate expectations.
fields.name: Integrity

fields.definition: Able to delegate, inspire and communicate effectively.
fields.name: Leadership Skills

fields.definition: Being able to understand the other side's motivations and leverage and reach a win-win resolution that you find favorably, satisfies both sides, and maintains relationships for future interactions.
fields.name: Negotiating

fields.definition: An individual's common sense about people that enables them to be interpersonally appropriate and aware. Tend to know what is happening in a group situation and how to deal with others in the most effective way. They ask good questions, listen to what others are saying, and stay engaged in conversations intently.
fields.name: People Smart

fields.definition: Able to manage an ongoing process of communication between a supervisor and an employee that occurs throughout the year, in support of accomplishing the strategic objectives of the organization. The communication process includes clarifying expectations, setting objectives, identifying goals, providing feedback, and reviewing results.
fields.name: Performance Management

fields.definition: Approaches others in a pleasant, upbeat manner; maintains enthusiasm despite challenges and/or criticism of ideas.
fields.name: Positive Attitude

fields.definition: Effectively presenting your work results and ideas formally to an audience that captivates their attention, engage their input, and motivates them to act in accordance to your desired outcome.
fields.name: Presentation Skills

fields.definition: Able to recognize and use information about organizational climate and key individuals to accomplish legitimate organizational goals; be aware of the importance of timing, politics, and group processes in managing change.
fields.name: Reading the System

fields.definition: Able to work on important issues first, staying with a plan of action or point of view until the desired goal has been obtained or is no longer reasonably attainable. Can recognize opportunities, act on them, and look for ways to quickly overcome barriers. Able to persevere in the face of adversity or opposition.
fields.name: Results Focused

fields.definition: Able to work with others to achieve a common aim; using their individual skills and providing constructive feedback, despite any personal conflict between individuals.
fields.name: Teamwork

fields.definition: Able to withhold action or speech in the absence of important information; deal with unresolved situations, frequent change, delays or unexpected events.
fields.name: Tolerance of Ambiguity

fields.definition: Able to provide organized activity aimed at imparting information and/or instructions to improve the recipient's performance or to help them attain a required level of knowledge or skill. Can develop tip sheets and other training materials.
fields.name: Trainer/Teaching Skills
One year current experience in specialty.
Active LPN license in the state of Kansas.
Experience with Ruby on Rails development
B.S. or B.A. degree or higher.
